13. Rg1! { A very strong move! The idea is to defend the g4-pawn so that we can soon push our f-pawn. White is doing really well here because Black has been unable to pose any threat to our space advantage on both the centre and kingside. } Rfe8 { Black plays a natural-looking move, but already White can break through. } 
14. Bxb6! { It's good to begin by exchanging the bishops, since that way our queen is no longer tied down to the defense of the bishop. } axb6 
15. f4 $16  { White's attack is finally gaining steam and Black can only sit back and hope that we mess it up. Black is much worse and will have trouble avoiding a quick defeat against best play. } *

