12. Qd2 } { Most of the time, we'll play this move. We empty the d1-square for our rook to occupy it in some lines, and at the same time, we're also now defending the knight on e3. } Nc5 
13. Be2 $16  { White has a great position here due to the extra space, with simple moves like O-O and a possible queenside expansion on the horizon. } f5 { Often Black goes for this pawn break, seeking to challenge our space advantage. However, it's a case of the cure being worse than the disease. } 
14. exf5! { We switch gears, and now if Black wants to win their pawn back, they will have to give up their bishop. } Bxf5 
15. Nxf5 Rxf5 
16. O-O $16  } { White stands much better, with 17.f4! next being our likely move, opening up the scope of our bishop on e2. Long-term, Black has some significant problems because of their vulnerable kingside and weak light squares. } *

