13. Rb1 { Stepping onto the semi-open file. This move also contains a clever idea which we'll see in the next move. } d6 { Black seeks to finish their development. } 
14. Rb3+- } -- ( { This is our very strong idea. It turns out that Black's queen on g6 is not very safe, with } 14...-- 15.Rg3 { likely coming next. White is down only one pawn, and in exchange, has a much safer king, the bishop pair, and much healthier development. Objectively Black is lost, though, of course, the position remains very sharp. } )
