7. Bd3 } ( { Once again, we are threatening f4. Black has a few things they can do here, most of the time, they just err immediately with } 7...a6? { when after } 8.f4 { , we kick the queen away and take on c7 after that, winning the game. That said, even if Black avoids this, we will get a really nice position. For example, the game could continue as follows. } ) { Defending c7. } 
8. f4 { Playing this move anyway, grabbing space and gaining time against Black's queen. } Qe7 
9. O-O+- } { White has a crushing development and space advantage. } *

