13. Bb2+- -- ( 13...Qxb4 { will fail to } 14.Qb5+ Qxb5 15.Bxb5 c6 16.Bxd4 { hitting g7, so White emerges a piece up. } { Therefore, Black has to give up their queen with 13...Qxb2 and White is left with a big advantage since the queen is especially effective in a position where Black’s development is poor and there are a lot of targets to attack. } )
