{ White to play and win! } 14. Bxf6! } { Eliminating a key defender. } Bxf6 
15. Ne4! } Re7? ( { Bringing the knight into the game and creating all sorts of threats. One fancy threat is } 15...-- 16.Rxd7 Qxd7 17.Qxf6! { winning two bishops for a rook. } ) ( { In the game, Black panicked with this poor defense, though even after the best move } 15...Rb4! { Black's position is lost since White's pieces are just too strong. } 16.b3! { Simplest. Black has nothing better here than to give up the exchange on c4 to blunt the attack, but then the material difference should decide the game in White's favour. } ) 
16. Nxf6+ gxf6 
